def correlation_matrix(df):
    from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
    from matplotlib import cm as cm
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(111)
    cmap = cm.get_cmap('jet', 30)
    cax = ax1.imshow(df, interpolation="nearest", cmap=cmap)
    ax1.grid(True)
    plt.title('Matrix de Correlation ')
    labels = ['','Reykjavik','Oslo','Paris','New York','Tunis','Alger', 'Beyrouth','Atlan27N40W','Dakar',]
    ax1.set_xticklabels(labels,fontsize=6)
    ax1.set_yticklabels(labels,fontsize=6)
    # Add colorbar, make sure to specify tick locations to match desired ticklabels
    fig.colorbar(cax, ticks=[.75,.8,.85,.90,.95,1])
    plt.show()

def caracteriserLesDonnees(x,y):
    #if not(len(x.shape)==1) & not(len(y.shape)==1) & len(x)==len(y)):
    #if ~(isvector(x) & isvector(y) & len(x)==len(y)):
    #    error('Pas coherent avec regression lineaire')

    n     = len(x)
    xMean = np.mean(x)
    sx2   = np.var(x,ddof=0)
    yMean = np.mean(y)
    sy2   = np.var(y,ddof=0)
    cxy   = np.cov(x,y,ddof=0)[0][1]
    #cxy   = scipy.cov(numpy.column_stack((x,y)))

    return n, xMean, yMean, sx2, sy2, cxy

def calculDeLEcartTypeDeA(s,sx2,n):
    
    return float('nan')

def intervalleDeConfiancePourA(a,n,sx2,s,risque):
    
    if risque < 0 or risque >1:
        print("probleme de risque")
        
    # ecart-type de a
    sa = calculDeLEcartTypeDeA(s,sx2,n)

    # ecart de student
    tAlpha_n = scipy.stats.t.ppf(1-risque/2, n-2)
    
    Ia_inf = a - tAlpha_n*sa
    Ia_sup = a + tAlpha_n*sa
    
    return Ia_inf,Ia_sup

intervalleDeConfiancePourA(a_o,tmp,sx2,s,0.5)
